  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">A shipping service restricts the dimensions of the boxes it will ship for a certain type of service. The&nbsp;restriction states that for boxes shaped like rectangular prisms, the sum of the perimeter of the base of the box and the height of the box cannot exceed 130&nbsp;inches. The perimeter of the base is determined using the width and length of the box. If&nbsp;a box has a height of 60&nbsp;inches and its length is 2.5&nbsp;times the width, which inequality shows the allowable width <span class=\"italic\">x</span>, in inches, of the box?</p>\n",
