  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. If <span class=\"italic\">x</span> is the width, in inches, of the box, then the length of the box is 2.5<span class=\"italic\">x</span> inches. It follows that the perimeter of the base is <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 times, open parenthesis, 2 point 5 x plus x, close parenthesis\"></span>, or 7<span class=\"italic\">x</span> inches. The height of the box is given to be 60 inches. According to the restriction, the sum of the perimeter of the base and the height of the box should not exceed 130 inches. Algebraically, this can be represented by <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"7 x plus 60, is less than or equal to 130\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"7 x is less than or equal to 70\"></span>. Dividing both sides of the inequality by 7 gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x is less than or equal to 10\"></span>. Since <span class=\"italic\">x</span> represents the width of the box, <span class=\"italic\">x</span> must also be a positive number. Therefore, the inequality <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"0 is less than x, which is less than or equal to 10\"></span> represents all the allowable values of <span class=\"italic\">x</span> that satisfy the given conditions.<p>Choices B, C, and D are incorrect and may result from calculation errors or misreading the given information.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
